wc [-l] [-w] [-c] <file>

  Count lines, words, and bytes in a file.

  Options:
    -l    print line count only
    -w    print word count only
    -c    print byte count only

  With no options, prints all three counts followed by the filename.
  Columns are right-aligned to 8 characters, matching POSIX output.

  Examples:
    wc /etc/hostname
    wc -l /sys/help/index
    wc -c /sys/welcome
